#Purpose
Catalogs stock items in inventory, allowing addition, updating, and removal of item records
#Design Decisions
Modular Design: The codebase is divided into functions and modules to enhance readability and maintainability.
Input Validation: Input validation is implemented to ensure that users provide valid row and column values when making reservations.
#Algorithms Used
NO
#Data Structures Employed
2d vector
map
file
#Functions/Modules Created
void add(const string& category, const Item& item)
void update(const string& category, const string& itemName, const Item& updatedItem)
void remov(const string& category, const string& itemName)
void removeCategory(const string& category)
void show()
void save(const string& filename)
void load(const string& filename)
#librarys used
#include <iostream>
#include <map>
#include <vector>
#include <list>
#include <string>
#include <algorithm>
